+## backup drive
+
+Creates a redacted backup package in a local folder. Point `--target` at a Google Drive sync folder to let Google Drive upload it.
+
+```text
+python pala.py backup drive --target "C:\Users\you\Google Drive\Pala Memory Core"
+```
+
+If no target is given, the default folder is:
+
+```text
+%USERPROFILE%\Documents\Pala Memory Core Drive Backup
+```
+
+Environment variable:
+
+```text
+PALA_DRIVE_BACKUP_PATH=C:\path\to\Google Drive\Pala Memory Core
+```
+
 ## dashboard export
 
 Writes today's local records to `dashboard/records.json` so the static dashboard can show real captured data.
