+## Drive Backup Behavior
+
+The first Drive connector writes a redacted package into a local folder. If that folder is inside Google Drive's desktop sync area, Google Drive handles upload.
+
+| Mode | Behavior |
+|---|---|
+| `backup drive --target <folder>` | Writes redacted package to chosen folder |
+| `PALA_DRIVE_BACKUP_PATH` | Sets default Drive backup folder |
+| future OAuth connector | Uploads directly through Google Drive API |
+
 ## Design Rule
 
 If a connector is fragile, keep it optional. The core should still work through manual capture and file import.
