+# v0.7 Drive Folder Backup
+
+Date: 2026-06-09
+Phase: Drive folder backup preview
+Status: PASS for local Drive-folder backup preview
+
+## Goal
+
+Create a Google Drive-compatible backup path without requiring OAuth by writing a redacted package into a chosen local folder.
+
+## Added Behavior
+
+| Area | Change |
+|---|---|
+| CLI | Added `python pala.py backup drive` |
+| Target | `--target <folder>` or `PALA_DRIVE_BACKUP_PATH` |
+| Default | `%USERPROFILE%\Documents\Pala Memory Core Drive Backup` |
+| Output | Dated package folder |
+| Safety | Uses the same redaction policy as GitHub backup |
+| Upload model | Google Drive desktop sync can upload the folder |
+
+## Command
+
+```powershell
+python .\pala.py backup drive --target .\data\backups\drive-smoke
+```
+
+## Expected Package
+
+| File | Purpose |
+|---|---|
+| `drive-backup-report.md` | Human-readable summary |
+| `records-manifest.json` | Redacted record manifest |
+| `drive-backup-receipt.json` | Backup receipt |
+| `artifacts/` | Redacted brief/receipt/dashboard exports when present |
+
+## Smoke Test
+
+```powershell
+python .\pala.py backup drive --target .\data\backups\drive-smoke
+python .\pala.py backup receipt
+python .\pala.py dashboard export
+```
+
+Observed output:
+
+```text
+drive backup package saved C:\Users\Pala-Home-1\Desktop\Codex\pala-memory-core\data\backups\drive-smoke\2026-06-09-20260609T133301Z-pala-memory-core-drive-backup
+records=4 artifacts=3
+receipt saved data\backups\2026-06-09-backup-receipt.md
+dashboard data saved dashboard\records.json
+```
+
+## Release Posture
+
+This is a local Drive-folder preview, not direct Google Drive API upload. Use a Google Drive sync folder as the target for cloud sync.
